<h3><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="color:#d3531a">FISHERY SECTOR IN INDIA</span></span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">India is 2nd largest fish producing country in the world,&nbsp;</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">8% of global fish production, sector contributes 1.1% to GDP, 5.15% to agri GDP</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Two primary fisheries - Inland Fisheries (2/3) and Marine Fisheries(1/3)</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">helpful in development of &nbsp;Blue &nbsp;economy</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">economic survey 2020 only 58% of the country’s&nbsp;inland <strong>potential</strong> has been tapped so far.</span></span></p>
<h3><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">major transformation in fisheries in past years:</span></span></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:medium">growth of inland aquaculture, Freshwater</span></p></li>
<li>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size:medium">Mechanisation in capture</span></p></li>
<li>Brackish water shrimp aquaculture&nbsp;</li></ul>
<p>to provide additional impetus to Matasya sampada:</p>
<ol>
<li>support to inland fisheries to transform Namami Gange to arth Ganga</li>
<li>modernisation of fishing &nbsp;harbours - Kochi Chennai Visakhapatnam Paradip petuaghat</li>
<li>hub n sopke spoke model in Tamil Nadu for multipurpose seaweed Park</li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Challenges :</span></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Enhanced human activity in aquatic areas - leads to occurrence of dead zone/ Hypoxic zones leading to permanent loss of fishing zones</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">ill effects on marine culture - pollution</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Loss of habitat and indiscriminate fishing</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Lack of quality seed and feed for fish</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Inadequate availability of credit</span></span></li></ul>
<h3><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Govt steps taken :</span></span></h3>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">PM MATASYA SAMPADA - double Marine exports to $15 billion by 2024</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif">matsya setu app - species by use module for fisheries management by NFDB</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Budget - Extend facility of Kisan Credit Cards to fisheries sector (working capital needs)</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">FIDF - for aquaculture infra development +&nbsp;reduce post harvest loss</span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Blue Revolution scheme Neel Kranti mission -for infrastructure in fisheries, food and nutrition security</span></span></li></ul>
<h4><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Inland fishing</span></span></h4>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Committee under Dr. Dilip Kumar to draft a national policy on inland fishing.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">“Development of Inland Fisheries and Aquaculture” Scheme for inland fishing</span></span></p>
<h4><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Marine Fishing</span></span></h4>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">National Policy on Marine Fishing 2017</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">"Letter of Permit"(LOP) system in EEZ has been stopped to boost livelihood of local fishermen</span></span></p>
<h4><br />
tech for fisheries&nbsp;</h4>
<ul>
<li>impact based weather&nbsp;forecasting IMD, GAGAN devices, PFZ, food processing tech n cold storage,&nbsp;</li></ul>
<h3><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Way forward :</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Dr.B Meenakumari committee - recco can be implemented for creation of buffer zone (b/w 200m and 500m) and scientific use of fishing net</span></span></p>
<p><span style="color:#2ecc71">Include fishermen in definition of PM KISAN &nbsp;for income support&nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin-left:40px">MAHI (monthly average household income) of farmer - 6500 , MAHI of fisherman - 4400 , NSSO</p>
<p><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">Use of Fish Aggregating Devices (FADs) and Artificial Reefs (ARs) for stock enhancement</span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="color:#1abc9c"><span style="font-family:Trebuchet MS,Helvetica,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12pt">transforming matasya&nbsp;Sampada to matsya samridhi&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>